        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued September 8 at 10:16PM CDT until September 8 at 11:15PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>SVRAMA

The National Weather Service in Amarillo has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northeastern Hemphill County in the Panhandle of Texas...

* Until 1115 PM CDT.

* At 1016 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 5 miles east of
Lake Marvin, or 17 miles east of Canadian, moving southeast at 25
mph.

HAZARD...Two inch hail and 70 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect some tree damage. Damage is likely to mobile
homes, roofs, and outbuildings. People and animals
outdoors will be injured. Expect hail damage to roofs,
siding, windows, and vehicles.

* This severe thunderstorm will remain over mainly rural areas of
northeastern Hemphill County.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
